creditline: Gift of Mr.  Augustus L. Searle
description: Dish, white camphor jade (one of a pair 36.7.2-3).  Carved in chrysanthemum form and worked to proper thinness. One of pair has a small hole the size of a pin prick, which appears to have been done at time.  Rough carving, but may be the result of [moving?].
title: Dish
